result.answer: Yes.  The documents describe ragas (the plural of “rag”) as useful melodic frameworks in Indian classical music — they can be performed on many instruments or sung, and they are employed specifically to evoke particular emotions in listeners.  Those qualities indicate that a rag is regarded as a positive (i.e., “good”) musical element.
